name: grass silage production, organic | grass silage, organic | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/50/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of grass silage (dry matter). The dry matter yield is 8100 kg/ha. Moisture content at storage is 65%.;;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

Grass silage is assumed to be composed of grass from 'grass production, organic, intensive' (20%), 'grass production, permanent grassland, organic, extensive' (40%) and from 'grass production, permanent grassland, organic, intensive' (40%). In the first case the process starts with the establishment of a temporary meadow, in the latter two cases an established grassland is the starting point. Find details in the respective datasets.


The dataset includes all machine operations of the contributing grass production systems in fractions as shown in 'included activities start'. Additionally, the processes of swathing, haying, baling, loading of bales and transport to the farm (1 km) are included. This activity ends after loading of bales at the farm gate.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0119:Growing of other non-perennial crops

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Refers to a production in the Swiss plateau (lowlands <700m).
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data were compiled from statistics, fertilising recommendations, documents from extension services and expert knowledge.
